Adjust rack to top position and preheat  oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Cut @potatoes{12%ounce} into 1⁄2-inch-thick wedges. Pick @parsley{1/4%ounce} leaves from stems; discard stems and finely chop leaves. Trim and thinly slice @scallions{2}, separating whites from greens; finely chop whites. Quarter @lime{1}.

Toss potatoes on a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of @cooking oil{1%tablespoon}, half the @garlic powder{1%teaspoon}, @salt{}, and @pepper{}. Roast on top rack until browned and tender, ~{20-25%minutes}.

While potatoes roast, in a #small bowl{}, combine parsley, scallion whites, remaining garlic powder, @olive oil{2%tablespoon}, @red wine vinegar{2%teaspoon}, a pinch of @chili flakes{1%teaspoon}, salt, and pepper. (Save remaining vinegar and chili flakes for another use.) Taste and adjust seasonings as you like.

Set aside, stirring occasionally, until ready to serve.

Pat @bavette steak{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{} and season generously all over with salt and pepper.

Heat a drizzle of oil in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add steak and cook to desired doneness, ~{5-7%minutes} per side.

Turn off heat; transfer steak to a #cutting board{}. Wipe out pan.

Drain @corn{1}; pat dry with paper towels.

Heat a drizzle of oil in pan used for steak over high heat. Add corn and cook, stirring occasionally, until golden brown and lightly charred in spots, ~{3-5%minutes}. TIP: If corn begins to pop, cover pan.

Transfer corn to a #medium bowl{} and stir in scallion greens, @mayonnaise{2%tablespoon}, half the @chili powder{1%teaspoon}, @sugar{1/4%teaspoon}, a squeeze of lime juice, salt, and pepper. TIP: If you like things spicy, add some @?chili flakes{}!

Thinly slice steak crosswise.

Divide steak, potatoes, and corn salad between plates. Spoon chimichurri over steak and serve with remaining lime wedges on the side.

> Steak is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 145°.